description: In Andhra Pradesh's Guntur, a group of determined female engineering students are working as janitors and performing other chores at their college to afford hostel fees. Coming from financially challenged backgrounds, these students willingly clean toilets, water plants, and assist in the kitchen to ease the burden on their families and continue their education.
title: Band of BTech students in Andhra forced to double up as janitors

description: Despite Congress's claim that PM Modi reversed his stance on caste enumeration due to their pressure, the party highlighted the government's 2021 decision against a caste census and its plea to the Supreme Court to avoid ordering one. Congress is now questioning Modi's apparent U-turn and directing state units to rally for caste census implementation and the removal of reservation barriers.
title: Caste census: Cong targets BJP with SC affidavit, Parl reply

description: Mohammad Asif Qamar, an IIT Kharagpur student, tragically died by suicide in his hostel room during a video call with a friend in Delhi, who alerted authorities. This incident, the second in a short period, has prompted IIT Kharagpur to form a committee to investigate the rising number of suicides on campus. While no prior mental health concerns were identified, Qamar had faced an exam malpractice issue earlier this year.
title: IIT-Kharagpur student found dead in hostel

description: Chhattisgarh's Chief Minister Vishnu Deo Sai initiated the state's first AI-based Data Centre Park in Nava Raipur, featuring a unique 2.7-hectare SEZ for AI services. With a proposed investment of Rs 1,000 crore over two years, the project aims to transform the state into a digital hub, empowering youth, farmers, and tribal communities.
title: India's first AI-based data park to come up in Raipur

description: In Madhya Pradesh's Guna district, police rescued sixteen mentally challenged and destitute men from modern-day slavery, some held for as long as two decades. They were trapped in a brutal exploitation system called 'Rahua,' forced to work long hours for mere food and shelter, often alongside cattle.
title: MP police rescue 16 from slavery in Guna, arrest 11

description: NEET-UG 2025 witnessed a decline in attendance, recording 91.4% with 20.8 lakh candidates appearing out of 22.7 lakh registered, attributed to NTA's stringent checks to eliminate "bogus" candidates. Enhanced security measures, including mobile jammers and biometric authentication, were implemented across 5,453 exam centers. A centralized control room and coordinated efforts with various ministries ensured real-time monitoring and action against false information on social media.
title: NEET-UG sees lowest attendance since 2021

description: Odisha government plans to request West Bengal to stop referring to the Digha temple as "Jagannath Dham," sparking political disputes. Allegations of using Puri temple wood for Digha idols are under investigation, while craftsmen dismiss the claims. Opposition parties criticize the BJP for its handling of the sensitive issue, emphasizing the emotional connection of Odias to Jagannath culture.
title: Odisha to Bengal: Stop calling Digha temple Jagannath Dham

description: The Supreme Court has affirmed that in gangrape cases, proving each accused committed the complete act of rape isn't necessary for conviction. The court emphasized that if one member of a group commits rape with shared intent, all involved are equally responsible and punishable under Section 376(2)(g) of IPC, highlighting the principle of joint liability based on common intention.
title: Rape by one of a gang makes others responsible, equally punishable: SC

description: Alcohol prices in India vary significantly across states due to differing excise duties and taxes, with Goa having the lowest levies. This disparity undermines the 'one nation, one tax' principle, encouraging bootlegging and revenue loss for high-tax states. Industry bodies advocate for tax rationalization to promote sustainable revenue growth and discourage excessive consumption, but finance ministers are hesitant to relinquish taxation powers.
title: Rs100 in Goa & Rs305 in Karnataka, excise duty difference defeats spirit of '1 nation, 1 tax'

description: In a tragic incident at Mahatma Gandhi Memorial Medical College and Hospital in Jamshedpur, a third-floor balcony collapsed, resulting in the death of three patients and injuries to two others. Authorities have launched an investigation into the accident, and the state government has announced compensation for the victims' families and the injured. Rescue teams safely evacuated ten patients from the affected medicine ward.
title: Three dead, two hurt in Jharkhand hospital roof collapse

description: A Thane-based lawyer was allegedly attacked and molested on the Mumbai-Indore Avantika Express. Co-passengers, Imtiyaz Odiya and Rubina Yusuf Pathan, reportedly disrobed her, slashed her with a blade, and threatened her after accusing her of theft. Police arrested Pathan and Odiya, invoking charges including assault and outraging a woman's modesty.
title: Woman disrobed, attacked and molested in train, 2 arrested

description: BJP has praised a Sikh student for questioning Rahul Gandhi about the 1984 Sikh massacre during an interaction at Brown University. The student challenged Gandhi on reconciliation efforts with the Sikh community, citing past Congress actions and impunity for leaders like Sajjan Kumar. BJP criticized Gandhi's response and also attacked him for referring to Lord Ram as a mythological figure during the same event.
title: BJP: Rahul Gandhi ridiculed not just in India, but globally

description: Following the apprehension of a Pakistan Rangers trooper by BSF personnel, the wife of detained BSF jawan Purnam Kumar Shaw expresses renewed hope for her husband's return. Rajani Shaw believes this incident may prompt negotiations between the BSF and Pakistan Rangers, potentially leading to an exchange of prisoners. Frustrated by the lack of progress, she plans to meet with BSF officers in Delhi if there are no updates.
title: BSF jawan’s kin see glimmer of hope in Pak trooper’s capture

description: Ferozepur Cantonment, near the India-Pakistan border, experienced a 30-minute blackout drill reminiscent of the 1971 War. Residents were informed beforehand about the exercise, which involved switching off all lights, including generators. Checkpoints were active, and hooters sounded, creating an atmosphere of emergency. The Cantonment Board stated the drill was a routine safety measure, thanking residents for their cooperation.
title: Echoes of 1971 as Ferozepur Cantt goes dark in 30-minute drill

description: Amid escalating tensions, the IAF chief briefed PM Modi on operational readiness, including long-range fighter sorties and heightened air defense. This meeting, following a similar briefing from the Navy chief, underscores India's preparedness for potential punitive strikes against Pakistan. The IAF is conducting regular combat air patrols and increasing operational readiness platforms, with Rafales equipped for swift action.
title: IAF chief briefs PM Modi on force's op readiness

description: Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi is scheduled to visit Pakistan on Monday, followed by a trip to India later in the week. The visit occurs amidst heightened tensions between India and Pakistan following the Pahalgam terror attack. While in Pakistan, Araghchi will engage in discussions on bilateral relations and the regional situation, while the India visit is for a pre-scheduled joint commission meeting.
title: Iran min to visit India & Pak; govt rules out mediation

description: Defence Minister Rajnath Singh has assured India that a "befitting reply" will be given to those responsible for the Pahalgam massacre, indicating potential military action against Pakistan. He emphasized PM Modi's leadership and determination to fulfill the people's desires for retribution. This statement follows discussions with the US Secretary of Defence, where Singh highlighted Pakistan's role in supporting terrorism.
title: Rajnath Singh: 'Under PM Modi, you'll get the Pahalgam hitback you want'

description: Zeba Afroz, a schoolteacher in Sonbhadra, has been suspended following complaints about her "objectionable remarks" on social media concerning a Navy official killed in the Pahalgam terror attack. The basic education officer took immediate action due to the comments being against service rules. An investigation is underway, and further action will be determined based on the investigation report.
title: School teacher suspended in UP for remarks against Pahalgam victim

description: In Amritsar, Punjab Police arrested Phalak Sher Masih and Suraj Masih for allegedly leaking sensitive information and photographs of Indian military and security installations to Pakistani handlers. The duo, apprehended in Bahlarwal village, transmitted the data via WhatsApp and received payments for their actions. Investigations revealed their connection to a cross-border smuggler currently incarcerated in Amritsar Central Jail.
title: Two men held in Punjab for leaking intel to Pakistani handlers

description: In a shocking incident in Amethi, a dispute over tandoori rotis at a wedding escalated into a brutal lynching, resulting in the deaths of cousins Ashish, 17, and Ravi, 18. The young men were attacked with iron rods and lathis after a verbal spat at the food stall. Police have registered a case against 13 individuals and detained several suspects as investigations continue into this senseless act of violence.
title: 2 teens lynched after brawl over tandoori roti at Amethi wedding

description: Telangana's draft bill on gig workers revives the debate once led by Rajasthan, where a pioneering 2023 law remains stalled. Gig workers in Rajasthan struggle with low earnings and lack of social security, as the promised welfare measures face bureaucratic delays. Amidst this, a cooperative framework and union efforts offer a glimmer of hope for a more equitable future.
title: 2 years on, Telangana gig workers' Bill catches Rajasthan's landmark law 'napping'

description: Achchhan Khan, a former Congress Seva Dal official, has been sentenced to life imprisonment by a special court in Ambedkar Nagar for raping a Dalit woman who was also a party worker. The court also imposed a fine of Rs 22,000.
title: After 7 years, ex-Congress man gets life in prison for rape of Dalit woman

description: In 2015, Pramod Kumar of Bulandshahr was sentenced to rigorous life imprisonment by a fast-track court for burning his four-month-pregnant wife, Jaya Devi, to death over dowry demands. Jaya, who was 32 years old, succumbed to her injuries at a Delhi hospital after suffering 85% burns. The court also imposed a fine of Rs 17,000 on the convict, emphasizing the societal implications of the crime.
title: Man in UP gets life in jail for burning pregnant wife over dowry in 2015

description: The Bombay High Court has denied an IIT aspirant's plea to take the JEE (Advanced) exam after the National Testing Agency (NTA) flagged his JEE (Mains) scorecard as a 'case of unfair means' (UFM). The court upheld NTA's decision, finding no reason to doubt the agency's assessment or interfere with the UFM designation, while keeping open the option for the student to challenge his debarment separately.
title: NTA’s task, says HC, refuses to assess IIT aspirant’s score

description: Eight districts in Haryana are grappling with a severe drinking water crisis as Punjab refuses to release additional water from the Bhakra Dam. These districts, including Sirsa and Hisar, are receiving only 15% of their required water supply, leaving 156 waterworks tanks dry.
title: Punjab cuts supply, 8 Haryana districts face water crisis

description: Punjab's assembly will convene a special session due to a water-sharing dispute with Haryana, triggered by the Centre's directive for Punjab to release additional water. Punjab is resisting, claiming it lacks surplus water, leading to escalated tensions ahead of annual water allocation. Political solidarity is seen in Punjab, while Haryana defends its demand, intensifying the conflict.
title: Special session of Punjab House today to discuss water release to Haryana

description: In Bareilly, a dentist named Ravendra Prakash Sharma has been sentenced to 10 years in jail and fined Rs 25,000 for raping a 28-year-old married woman after sedating her during a treatment in October 2021. The court found him guilty of rape and criminal intimidation, considering the impact on the victim's married life and the circumstantial evidence presented.
title: UP dentist gets 10 years in jail for raping woman in clinic

description: Farooq Yasin Mansoor, a key suspect in the 1993 Bombay blasts, has been convicted and sentenced to five years for using a forged passport to enter India from Dubai in 2018. Although he has already served the time as an undertrial, Mansoor will remain in custody due to his ongoing trial in connection to the blasts case.
title: 1993 Bombay blasts conspirator Farooq Takla found guilty of passport forgery

description: Following a recent student suicide, the third in five months, BITS Pilani K K Birla Goa Campus is implementing several measures to support student well-being. These include curriculum revisions, offering exam flexibility for distressed students, and developing a 'Student Wellbeing Dashboard' for personalized support. The institution is also introducing new courses on mental and physical wellness and stress management.
title: After 3 suicides, BITS Pilani-Goa includes stress management in syllabus

description: Assam Police took swift action following a torture allegation. The incident involved Sanjit Moran at Bordumsa police station in Tinsukia. Five police personnel faced suspension, including sub-inspectors Jayanta Kalita and Rajib Deka. Constables Bishal Jyoti Basudev Boro, Bhaiti Das, and Rajib Deka were also suspended. An inquiry is underway, and authorities promise strict action if the allegations hold true. Locals protested, demanding justice for Moran.
title: Assam Police suspend 5 cops, including 2 SIs, after youth ‘tortured’ in police station

description: The Bengal government and the SSC have filed a review petition in the Supreme Court, seeking modifications to the April 3 judgment that scrapped the 2016 recruitment panel. They aim to distinguish between tainted and untainted appointees, requesting clarifications on the new recruitment process. This action follows assurances from CM Mamata Banerjee to protesting teachers, with mixed reactions arising from those affected.
title: Bengal moves Supreme Court to modify order sacking teachers

description: Parameswaran Iyer has been appointed as India's temporary nominee to the International Monetary Fund board, preceding a crucial meeting regarding a $1.3 billion support package for Pakistan. India opposes this funding due to concerns about Pakistan's alleged support for terrorism, particularly after the Pahalgam attack. This appointment follows the dismissal of Krishnamurthy Subramanian.
title: Iyer named temp nominee to IMF board ahead of meet to decide on $1.3bn Pak aid

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar criticized Europe, stating India seeks partners, not hypocritical preachers. He emphasized the need for mutual understanding and sensitivity in international partnerships, particularly regarding differing perspectives on the Russia-Ukraine war and tensions with Pakistan. Jaishankar also advocated for realism in engaging with both Russia and the United States, focusing on shared interests.
title: 'Need partners, not preachers': EAM S Jaishankar hits out at Europe

description: Intelligence officials at Lengpui airport near Aizawl detained an American couple, Walter Frederick Kuhn and Sahron Clodfelter Kuhn, upon arrival for not possessing the mandatory Protected Area Permit (PAP). They were subsequently deported to the US on Saturday.
title: Officials detain US couple at Lengpui, deport them over permit breach

description: Landowners in Pune's Purandar taluka clashed with police during a drone survey for a proposed international airport, resulting in the death of an elderly woman and injuries to many, including police officers. The survey has been indefinitely postponed due to the violence and escalating political controversy. The administration is considering dialogues with landowners to resolve the issue.
title: One dead as Pune villagers battle cops over airport land survey

description: Bengal Governor CV Ananda Bose's report to Amit Shah on Murshidabad communal strife suggests President's rule if the situation worsens. The report recommends a judicial inquiry and central intervention. Trinamool Congress criticizes the report as politically motivated. BJP supports intervention due to law-and-order concerns. Congress focuses on ensuring fair elections. The governor visited affected areas after mob violence and suggested CAPF camps in sensitive zones.
title: President rule finds mention in Bengal guv’s report on Murshidabad violence

description: The Supreme Court will decide on Monday regarding interim orders on petitions challenging the Waqf Amendment Act, 2025, concerning its impact on traditional Islamic ties and religious freedom. The Centre defends the Act as secular, countering claims of religious interference and emphasizing the need to prevent misuse of the 2013 amendment, which allegedly led to encroachment on properties.
title: Supreme Court to decide today if interim order needed on waqf pleas
3 soldiers die as Army vehicle plunges into gorge

description: Following the death of Imtiyaz Ahmad Magray, detained during a counter-terrorism operation after the Pahalgam attack, the J&K government is facing calls for a judicial inquiry. Magray's body was found in a river, with police claiming he drowned while attempting to escape. Political figures express concern over alleged custodial deaths and the potential for collective punishment in the region.
title: Detained man ‘drowns trying to escape’, J&K government seeks judicial probe

description: The Election Commission of India is set to launch ECINET, a unified platform consolidating over 40 existing election-related apps and portals. This single-point app aims to simplify the user experience for nearly 100 crore electors and 26 lakh other stakeholders by providing easy access to electoral data and services.
title: EC's single-point application set to integrate existing 40 apps, portals

description: CRPF constable Munir Ahmad was dismissed for allegedly concealing his marriage to a Pakistani woman, despite claiming he informed the department and his wife's long-term visa was pending. He appealed to PM Modi and Amit Shah, stating he followed procedures and the High Court acknowledged his wife's stay. Ahmad maintains his wife wasn't overstaying as her LTV application was under consideration.
title: Jammu CRPF constable dismissed for marrying Pak cousin appeals for justice

description: Over 100 UK MPs and peers are pressing Foreign Secretary David Lammy to intervene for the release of Jagtar Singh Johal, a British Sikh imprisoned in India since 2017 on terrorism charges. Despite an acquittal in one case due to lack of evidence, Johal remains detained, with concerns raised about torture and forced confessions.
title: UK MPs demand release of jailed British Sikh facing terror charges in India

description: Rishabh Pant's struggles continued with a meager 18 runs against Punjab Kings, further disappointing LSG owner Sanjiv Goenka. His poor form, marked by a low strike rate and multiple single-digit scores, contrasts sharply with Punjab Kings' dominant batting performance, highlighted by Prabhsimran Singh's explosive 91, propelling them to a formidable total of 236.
title: Rishabh Pant fails yet again, LSG owner can’t hide disappointment – Watch

description: West Bengal Governor CV Ananda Bose has submitted a report to the Home Ministry regarding the Murshidabad riots, triggered by protests against the Waqf (Amendment) Act, 2025. The report warns of radicalisation and militancy in border districts, highlighting administrative failures and a lack of coordination during the violence that resulted in casualties.
title: Murshidabad riots: Bengal guv flags 'radicalisation' threat in report to MHA

description: Prabhsimran Singh's brilliant 91 propelled Punjab Kings to a 37-run victory over Lucknow Super Giants. His explosive innings, supported by Shashank Singh's cameo, lifted Punjab to 236/5. Arshdeep Singh's early wickets crippled Lucknow's chase, despite Ayush Badoni's valiant 74, restricting them to 199/7 and securing a crucial win for Punjab.
title: Prabhsimran Singh and Arshdeep Singh help PBKS beat LSG by 37 runs

description: Amid rising India-Pakistan tensions, Ferozepur Cantonment conducted a 30-minute blackout rehearsal to assess security readiness. The power outage, accompanied by hooters, was a routine drill, according to Deputy Commissioner Deepshikha Sharma, who assured residents there was no cause for alarm. Security measures were heightened, with police monitoring anti-social elements and the BSF increasing border patrols.
title: Ferozepur Cantonment conducts blackout drill amid rising India-Pak tensions

description: Following a deadly terror attack in Pahalgam, India has launched a comprehensive retaliation against Pakistan, encompassing economic, diplomatic, and logistical measures. New Delhi has imposed a blanket ban on trade, suspended mail exchanges, and prohibited Pakistani ships from docking at Indian ports.
title: Trade, water and airspace: How India put pressure on Pakistan after Pahalgam terror attack

description: Warren Buffett, the legendary investor and CEO of Berkshire Hathaway, will retire by the end of 2025, passing the reins to Greg Abel. Buffett transformed Berkshire into a diversified conglomerate, achieving staggering returns of 5,502,284% compared to the S&P 500's 39,054%.
title: 5.5 million percent returns: Why there will be no other investor like Buffett
Does Musk regret supporting Trump? Check out his answer

description: Prabhsimran Singh's explosive half-century powered Punjab Kings in their match against Lucknow Super Giants at Dharamsala. His impressive innings marked his third consecutive fifty in IPL 2025, equalling a record held by PBKS legends Chris Gayle and KL Rahul. Rishabh Pant of LSG chose to bowl first, as Punjab Kings aim to solidify their playoff position.
title: Gayle has company! Prabhsimran creates history for Punjab Kings
Hard-partying Kash: What's behind the nightclub controversy? Explained

description: Rinku Singh's exceptional fielding, including a crucial run-out and boundary save, propelled Kolkata Knight Riders to a thrilling one-run victory over Rajasthan Royals. His efforts, combined with Andre Russell's explosive half-century and Rinku's own vital cameo, helped KKR secure a narrow win. The victory lifted KKR to fifth place in the IPL standings, boosting their playoff aspirations.
title: 'I enjoy fielding more than batting': Rinku after KKR beat RR by 1 run

description: Prashant Kishor has criticized Lalu Prasad Yadav and Tejashwi Yadav for dynastic politics. He accuses them of ignoring Congress in Bihar. Kishor believes national security is the Centre's domain. He is set to debut in the upcoming Bihar elections with his Jan Suraaj party. Kishor has been touring Bihar and criticizing major political parties.
title: 'It's Lalu Yadav's party and his son will be the CM face': Prashant Kishor

description: Lucknow Super Giants chose to bowl first after winning the toss against Punjab Kings in Dharamsala. LSG captain Rishabh Pant cited potential early assistance for bowlers as the reason. LSG debutant Akash Singh, a left-arm pacer, and PBKS included Marcus Stoinis in their playing XI. Akash Singh's journey from a humble background to professional cricket is highlighted.
title: Meet Akash Maharaj Singh: Rishabh Pant's secret weapon

description: Preity Zinta, co-owner of Punjab Kings, was visibly astonished when Shashank Singh hit a massive six off Mayank Yadav that exited the HPCA Stadium during Sunday's match. The umpire called for a new ball as it landed outside the grounds. Lucknow Super Giants (LSG) chose to field first after winning the toss.
title: PBKS batter sends ball flying out of stadium – see Preity Zinta’s reaction

description: Riyan Parag shouldered the blame for Rajasthan Royals' narrow one-run defeat to Kolkata Knight Riders. Parag's impressive 95 couldn't secure the win as RR fell short chasing 207. He lamented his dismissal and miscalculation during the crucial 16th and 17th overs. Andre Russell's explosive 57 propelled KKR to their total, while RR's loss eliminated them from playoff contention.
title: 'I feel awful...': Riyan Parag takes blame for Rajasthan Royals one-run loss

description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra affirmed Congress's complete support for any governmental action responding to the Pahalgam terrorist attack, which resulted in 26 civilian deaths. The Congress Working Committee has passed a resolution reflecting this united stance. She expressed hope that the Union government would act decisively to avenge the killings of innocent civilians and firmly address Pakistan's support of terrorism.
title: Priyanka says Cong to back any action Centre takes to avenge Pahalgam

description: Kolkata Knight Riders secured a nail-biting one-run victory against Rajasthan Royals in a high-scoring IPL 2025 match. Andre Russell's explosive half-century and Rinku Singh's exceptional fielding proved crucial for KKR. Despite Riyan Parag's brilliant 95, RR fell short, as KKR's bowlers held their nerve to keep their playoff hopes alive.
title: Russell's blitz, Rinku's brilliance in the field keep KKR in IPL playoffs race

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu pledged retaliation against Yemen's Huthi rebels following a missile strike near Ben Gurion Airport. The missile, launched in support of Palestinians in Gaza, injured six and briefly halted flights. While the Israeli army attempted interception, the exact cause of the damage remains unclear, with Netanyahu promising future action against the group.
title: 'There will be many bangs': Netanyahu vows action after Huthi missile strike

description: Apple's iPhone 17 lineup may include an ultra-slim 'Air' model, but internal tests suggest a 20% reduction in battery life compared to other models. To address this, Apple is reportedly considering reviving the Smart Battery Case, specifically tailored for the iPhone 17 Air. Production allocation reflects caution, with only 10% dedicated to the slimmer version.
title: Apple ‘iPhone 17 Air’ rumours hint at this ‘Big’ problem, return of this product

description: Riyan Parag's explosive hitting display, including six consecutive sixes, electrified Eden Gardens during Rajasthan Royals' IPL 2025 match against Kolkata Knight Riders. Parag's onslaught came after Andre Russell propelled KKR to a formidable total. Despite Parag's heroics, Rajasthan Royals are out of the playoff race, but his performance showcased the league's thrilling talent.
title: Carnage at Eden Gardens! Riyan Parag smashes 6 sixes in a row

description: On an IndiGo flight from Delhi to Shirdi on May 2, 2025, a male passenger was arrested for allegedly molesting an air hostess. The inebriated man reportedly touched the crew member inappropriately near the aircraft's toilet. Upon landing, security apprehended the accused, who was then handed over to Rahata Police, where a molestation case was registered against him.
title: Drunk passenger detained for molesting air hostess on Indigo flight

description: Riyan Parag's old tweet about hitting four sixes in an over resurfaced after he smashed five sixes off Moeen Ali in an over at Eden Gardens. Parag reached his half-century and technically hit six sixes in six balls by dispatching Varun Chakaravarthy for a maximum in the following over.
title: 'Four sixes in an over': Riyan Parag's two-year-old prophecy comes true

description: Amid escalating tensions following the Pahalgam massacre, BJP spokesperson Pradeep Bhandari claimed that panic has gripped Pakistan's leadership. He alleged that Pakistani ministers and army generals are booking tickets to flee the country, fearing a decisive response from India under Prime Minister Modi's leadership.
title: 'Most of Pak army generals, ministers already booked ticket to leave country': BJP

description: President Trump stated he won't remove Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell before his term ends in 2026, despite calling him "a total stiff" and urging lower interest rates. Trump acknowledged Powell isn't a fan but anticipates eventual rate cuts. This declaration aims to reassure markets unsettled by Trump's trade policies, including tariffs on various countries, while trade negotiations continue.
title: Won’t fire ‘total stiff’ Fed chair Powell before term ends in 2026: Trump

description: Punjab Kings, fresh off a victory, are set to clash with Lucknow Super Giants in Dharamshala, a match crucial for IPL 2025 playoff aspirations. PBKS, currently fourth, relies on Shreyas Iyer's leadership and a strong bowling attack. The scenic HPCA Stadium in Dharamshala is set to join the IPL 2025 hosting roster as Punjab Kings take on Lucknow Super Giants in a crucial mid-table clash on Sunday evening — a fixture that could prove pivotal in shaping the playoff race.
title: 'Aaj haar gye to ... ': Goenka's hug for Rishabh Pant goes viral

description: Teenage sensation Vaibhav Suryavanshi, the 14-year-old Rajasthan Royals batsman, is facing a batting slump after his record-breaking century. Following a duck against Mumbai Indians and 4 runs against Kolkata Knight Riders, the team management is urging patience. Despite the recent setbacks, bowling coach Shane Bond emphasizes nurturing the young talent, shielding him from pressure, and allowing him to play freely.
title: After 11 sixes in one game, Vaibhav Suryavanshi flops twice in a row

description: During President Trump's 100th day in office, he highlighted Elon Musk's Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), which reportedly cut $160 billion in waste. As Musk transitions from his role, Fox News met with DOGE members, revealing shocking savings.
title: Elon Musk raises alarm on Panda grant fraud: They didn't even ...

description: A controversy flared in Karnataka after a student was asked to remove his 'janeu' before a NEET exam. The BJP protested outside the exam center. The Karnataka High Court is hearing a PIL about similar incidents during CET exams. Deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar opposed the removal of religious symbols during exams.
title: Karnataka NEET student made to remove 'janeu' before exam; BJP protests

description: Meta faces backlash after a major blunder in its antitrust trial, angering Apple, Google, and Snapchat. Poorly redacted documents exposed confidential competitor data, raising concerns about Meta's competence and respect for legal proceedings. This incident, coupled with past controversies like "Operation Ghostbusters" and data breaches, fuels skepticism about Meta's ability to safeguard sensitive information amid ongoing FTC scrutiny.
title: Meta’s huge mistake that left lawyers from Apple, Google and Snapchat very angry

description: Uttar Pradesh Congress President Ajay Rai criticized the BJP government's defense spending, particularly the Rafale deal, following the Pahalgam terror attack that killed 26.
title: 'Rafale jets miniature with chilly and lemon': UP Congress president's jibe at BJP

description: Andre Russell's explosive unbeaten 57 propelled Kolkata Knight Riders to a formidable 206/4 against Rajasthan Royals. Russell's innings, featuring six sixes, marked his entry into the 1000-run club at Eden Gardens. He attributed his success to smart decision-making against spinners, emphasizing his preference to attack them, crucial for KKR's playoff aspirations.
title: 'Still feeling like 27': Russell turns back the clock with six-sixes blitz

description: In a conversation with Bombay Sport Exchange, veteran administrator Ratnakar Shetty recounted Indian cricket's evolution from its humble beginnings. He highlighted the crucial financial support from royal families and corporate figures in the early days when BCCI operated with limited resources.
title: 'Test cricketers used to get Rs 50 per day, Ranji Trophy players Rs 5'

description: Asaduddin Owaisi has strongly denounced Pakistan, labeling it a “failed nation” and accusing it of fostering terrorism. He condemned communal divisions following the Pahalgam attack, urging unity against those who seek to weaken India. Opposition parties have pressed the government to take decisive action, ensuring justice for victims' families and eradicating terrorism, with full support pledged for governmental measures.
title: 'Failed nation, poor country': Owaisi tears into Pakistan

description: In a thrilling IPL match, 17-year-old Ayush Mhatre's impressive 94 nearly secured a CSK victory against RCB. Despite missing a century, his selfless play drew praise, including from Virender Sehwag, who noted Mhatre prioritized the team's needs. Mhatre and Jadeja's 114-run partnership brought CSK close to chasing 214, showcasing Mhatre's maturity and talent on the big stage.
title: 'He wasn't thinking about his 100': Sehwag lauds selfless Ayush Mhatre

description: Warren Buffett, the legendary investor, will retire as CEO of Berkshire Hathaway at the end of 2025, passing the reins to Greg Abel. This announcement, made at the annual shareholders' meeting, marks a significant transition after Buffett's 54-year tenure.
title: Warren Buffet has $169 billion net worth: A look at his investments

description: Kunal Singh Rathore, a 22-year-old wicketkeeper-batter from Kota, Rajasthan, made his IPL debut for Rajasthan Royals against Kolkata Knight Riders in IPL 2025. He was acquired for Rs 30 lakh, and is the first cricketer from Kota to secure an IPL contract. Rathore has played domestic cricket, scoring 254 runs in 12 T20 matches.
title: Who is Kunal Singh Rathore? Meet RR's IPL debutant from Kota

description: Air India flight AI139, flying from Delhi to Tel Aviv, was diverted to Abu Dhabi after a missile strike occurred near Tel Aviv airport on Sunday. The Boeing 787 was about an hour away from landing when the incident prompted the diversion while it was in Jordanian airspace. Consequently, the return flight from Tel Aviv to Delhi has been cancelled.
title: Air India flight from Delhi diverted after missile strike near Israeli airport

description: India's sexual health and wellness sector is experiencing rapid growth, fueled by increased awareness among younger generations and significant venture capital investments. Startups are addressing diverse needs, from fertility treatments to personal wellness products, leveraging telehealth and D2C models to overcome traditional barriers.
title: Desi startups making sexual health means Big Business

description: Ajinkya Rahane, Kolkata Knight Riders' captain, chose to bat first after winning the toss against Rajasthan Royals at Eden Gardens. KKR brought in Moeen Ali and Ramandeep Singh, aiming to set a strong total. Rajasthan Royals, led by Riyan Parag, made three changes, including Hasaranga's return. Rajasthan Royals, already out of playoff contention, made three changes to their line-up.
title: Eliminated but not done! Why Riyan Parag made 3 bold changes vs KKR
